:N: Initial Delta Hedge - Shares
:I: $delta=rseq(55,75)/100; $options=rseq(100,300); $ANS=-$delta*$options
:Q: You sold $options call options, each with delta $delta. How many shares to delta hedge?
:A: Shares = -delta * options = -$delta * $options = $ANS (buy shares since negative).
:T: 10
:E:

:N: Portfolio Delta
:I: $shares=rseq(500,1000); $calls_long=rseq(5,10); $call_delta=rseq(60,70)/100; $puts_short=rseq(3,8); $put_delta=rseq(-45,-35)/100; $mult=100; $ANS=$shares+$calls_long*$call_delta*$mult+$puts_short*(-$put_delta)*$mult
:Q: Long $shares shares, long $calls_long calls (\(\Delta\)=$call_delta), short $puts_short puts (\(\Delta\)=$put_delta). Portfolio delta?
:A: Delta = $shares + $calls_long*$call_delta*100 - $puts_short*$put_delta*100 = $ANS.
:T: 10
:E:

:N: Rebalancing Delta Hedge
:I: $prev_delta=rseq(55,65)/100; $new_delta=rseq(68,78)/100; $options=rseq(100,200); $ANS=-($new_delta-$prev_delta)*$options
:Q: Delta was $prev_delta, now $new_delta. You're short $options calls. Shares adjustment needed?
:A: Adjustment = -(new_delta - old_delta) * options = -($new_delta - $prev_delta) * $options = $ANS.
:T: 10
:E:

:N: Gamma P&L
:I: $gamma=rseq(2,5)/100; $dS=rseq(2,5); $options=100; $ANS=0.5*$gamma*$dS^2*$options
:Q: You're long 100 options with gamma $gamma. Stock moves $$dS. Gamma P&L?
:A: Gamma P&L = 0.5 * \(\Gamma\) * (\(\Delta\)S)^2 * options = 0.5 * $gamma * $dS^2 * 100 = $$ANS.
:T: 10
:E:

:N: Theta vs Gamma Tradeoff
:I: $gamma=rseq(3,6)/100; $S=50; $sigma=rseq(25,35)/100; $theta=-0.5*$S^2*$sigma^2*$gamma/365; $ANS=$theta
:Q: You're long gamma ($gamma). S=$50, \(\sigma\)=$sigma. Daily theta cost (using \(\theta\) ~ -Â½S^2\(\sigma\)^2\(\Gamma\)/365)?
:A: Daily theta = -0.5 * $S^2 * $sigma^2 * $gamma / 365 = $$ANS.
:T: 10
:E:

:N: Delta-Gamma Hedge
:I: $port_delta=rseq(400,600); $port_gamma=rseq(-30,-15); $opt1_delta=0.5; $opt1_gamma=0.04; $opt2_delta=0.3; $opt2_gamma=0.03; $n_opt1=-$port_gamma/$opt1_gamma; $residual_delta=$port_delta+$n_opt1*$opt1_delta; $ANS=-$residual_delta
:Q: Portfolio: \(\Delta\)=$port_delta, \(\Gamma\)=$port_gamma. Option1: \(\Delta\)=$opt1_delta, \(\Gamma\)=$opt1_gamma. First gamma-hedge with $n_opt1 Option1s. Remaining delta hedge (shares)?
:A: After gamma hedge, residual delta = $port_delta + $n_opt1*$opt1_delta = $residual_delta. Shares needed = $ANS.
:T: 10
:E:

:N: Vega Hedge
:I: $port_vega=rseq(-500,-200); $hedge_vega=rseq(15,25); $ANS=-$port_vega/$hedge_vega
:Q: Portfolio vega = $port_vega. Hedging option has vega $hedge_vega. Options needed for vega neutrality?
:A: Options = -Portfolio vega / Option vega = -$port_vega / $hedge_vega = $ANS.
:T: 10
:E:

:N: P&L Attribution - Delta
:I: $delta=rseq(400,600); $dS=rseq(-3,3); $ANS=$delta*$dS
:Q: Portfolio delta = $delta. Stock moved $$dS. Delta P&L contribution?
:A: Delta P&L = \(\Delta\) * \(\Delta\)S = $delta * $dS = $$ANS.
:T: 10
:E:

:N: P&L Attribution - Theta
:I: $theta=rseq(-200,-80); $days=rseq(1,5); $ANS=$theta*$days/365
:Q: Portfolio theta = $$theta per year. Over $days days, theta P&L?
:A: Theta P&L = \(\theta\) * days/365 = $theta * $days/365 = $$ANS.
:T: 10
:E:

:N: Pin Risk
:I: $K=50; $S_close=rseq(49.5,50.5); $options=rseq(50,150); $expected_exercise=($S_close>$K)?$options:0; $ANS=$expected_exercise
:Q: You're short $options calls at K=$50. Stock closes at $$S_close. Expected assignment?
:A: If S > K, expect full assignment = $expected_exercise options.
:T: 20
:E:

